@page
@model WebApplication3.Pages.ObedienceTrainersSchoolsModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "ObedienceTrainersSchools";
}
<div class="container">

    <h1>Obedience Trainers &amp; Schools</h1>
    <br />
    <h2>Obedience Trainers and Dog Training Schools in Melbourne</h2>
    <br />
    <p>Professional dog trainers understand that <a asp-page="./CertIIICourseContent">certification</a> is central to the quality and integrity of their services. Public perception plays an important role in the success of professional careers in the provision of canine obedience training.</p>
    <p>Quality certification through an <a asp-page="./CertIIIGeneralInformation">accredited provider</a> is key to building a cohesive and sustainable professional profile in your community. Access to up to date industry knowledge through an NDTF training course is the best thing you can do for your business.</p>
    <p>The <a asp-page="./Index">National Dog Training Federation</a> (NDTF) represents and certifies individual dog trainers and dog training organisation throughout Australia. Our professional dog trainer certificates are a nationally recognised and government-approved seal of quality for any trainer. Those who we certify are considered the best in the business.</p>
    <br />
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xl-6 col-lg-6 col-md-12 col-sm-12">
            <h3>Exclusive Dog Obedience Certification</h3>
            <p>To receive certification from the NDTF, individuals or businesses must meet stringent standards of quality in their practices, services, and results in obedience training for dogs. The NDTF’s professional dog trainer certification is the highest recommendation for you or your business’s services and as providers of this training, it is imperative that we maintain these high standards ourselves.</p>
            <p>With widespread support across Australia, joining the NDTF ensures you are part of a network of dog trainers committed to excellence ethical practice and high standards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xl-6 col-lg-6 col-md-12 col-sm-12">
            <h3>Certification Requirements for Businesses</h3>
            <p>To achieve certification, a business must prove that all individuals employed by that company are worthy of our recommendation. This ensures that the entire organisation meets our strict criteria and that all their instructors’ meet a minimum standard of education and expertise. With all members on board you can be sure your business will benefit holistically from the professional development and support offered by the NDTF and move forward together as a team.</p>
        </div>
        <br />
        <h3>Get in Touch</h3>
        <p>The NDTF offers expert dog training to those who wish to gain understanding and experience with canine obedience, professionally or personally. You can access this training wherever you are across Australia, through our <a asp-page="./CertIIIDistanceLearningCourse">dog training distance education program</a>. For those based in Melbourne, you can attend <a asp-page="./CertIIIMelbourneLocalCourse">our training Centre</a> in person.</p>
        <p>The NDTF understand you may have questions and we are here to help with all of your enquiries.  If you would like to find out more about NDTF certification for yourself or your dog training business, contact us today on <b>1300 664 466</b> or <a asp-page="./ContactUs">enquire online</a> to find out more about the application process.</p>

        <br />

        <form method="post" asp-page="./ContactUs" asp-page-handler="Add">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="@Model.CVM.Fullname">Firstname</label>
                <input class="form-control" asp-for="@Model.CVM.Fullname" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="@Model.CVM.Email">Email</label>
                <input class="form-control" asp-for="@Model.CVM.Email" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="@Model.CVM.Subject">Subject</label>
                <input class="form-control" asp-for="@Model.CVM.Subject" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="@Model.CVM.Message">Message</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" asp-for="@Model.CVM.Message"></textarea>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" value="Add" class="btn btn-success" />
        </form>
    </div>
</div>